TITLE: Rishi Sunak poised to win UK prime minister spot after Boris Johnson drops
SUMMARY: Former finance minister Rishi Sunak is widely expected to secure the U.K. prime minister spot after Boris Johnson dropped out of the race. Sunak is running on economic caution.

TITLE: Iran's assistance to Russian war effort could make the country an enemy combatant, experts say
SUMMARY: Iran has supplied Russia with drones and other military equipment for its war in Ukraine that could open the country up to being considered a combatant in the conflict.

TITLE: Australian men face charges after blinding e-scooter rider with projectile potato
SUMMARY: Two men in Australia were arrested and charged after firing potatoes at people riding e-scooters. A young man was hit in the face and had to have surgery to remove one of his eyes.

TITLE: US, Russian defense secretaries speak for second time in three days amid 'dirty bomb' claims
SUMMARY: Lloyd Austin, the U.S. Secretary of Defense, spoke with his Russian counterpart for the second time in three days on Sunday, according to the Pentagon.

TITLE: North Korean ship crosses sea boundary, South Korean ships fire warning shots: report
SUMMARY: South Korea fired warning shots at a North Korean merchant ship early Monday after the vessel violated the country's territorial waters, according to the military.

TITLE: Russian fighter jet crashes into residential building in Siberian city
SUMMARY: A Russian Su-30 fighter jet crashed into a residential building in the Siberian city of Irkutsk on Sunday during a training flight, killing both pilots on board.

TITLE: Ukraine calls for global ban of Russia’s RT after commentator calls for Ukrainian kids to be drowned, burned
SUMMARY: Ukraine's foreign ministry is calling for a global ban on Russia's state-owned RT after one of its presents called for Ukrainian kids to be drowned.

TITLE: Boris Johnson announces he will not run to be next UK prime minster
SUMMARY: Former British Prime Minister Boris Johnson pulled himself out of the race to lead the Conservative Party on Sunday, ending speculation about a possible comeback.

TITLE: German climate change activists splash mashed potatoes on Monet painting
SUMMARY: Climate change activists on Sunday threw mashed potatoes on a Monet painting in a German museum and glued their hands on the wall to protest fuel extraction.

TITLE: Police apologize, pay Christian evangelist who was wrongfully arrested twice
SUMMARY: A female Christian evangelist in the United Kingdom garnered an apology from police in London and £10,000 in compensation after she was wrongfully arrested twice in 2020.
